Solving problems and knowing you've created something that will be productively used by another person is simultaneously exciting and empowering. Coding is one of the easiest ways to solve practical problems. If you consider any other type of engineering, you need some sort of raw material- wires, components, large machines and specially made parts to create whatever design you have in your head. But coding only needs a computer and good imagination and the end product depends only upon how good your idea is, and then Sky is the limit. Most fascinating thing about programming which I personally think is thinking itself, it broadens minds.
And one thing worth noting about coding would be how a small problem can propagate and leads to big error
